<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; WALLOWING IN HISTORY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  Zegrahm DeepSea Voyages is offering a nine-day cruise to see
the wreckage of the Titanic, beginning August 20, for $32,000 a
passenger. Twelve passengers will set out from St. John's,
Newfoundland, and ferry overnight to a research ship of the P.P.
Shirshov Institute of Oceanography in Moscow, which is anchored
near the Titanic.
</P>
<P>
   For six days, reports Men's Journal, groups including two
passengers and one leader will descend in MIR submersibles in
eight-hour dives to see the wreckage of the Titanic.
</P>
<P>
   When not undersea, the vacationers will attend lectures, have
access to the ship's extensive Titanic library, &LR;  and ``join
scientists in on-board marine laboratories.'' More information is
available at (206) 285-3743.
</P>
<P>
   _ New Yorker writer  &UR; Janet Malcolm &LR;  has written a parody of New
Yorker writer  &UR; Lillian Ross &LR; ' ``Here But Not Here,'' a memoir about
her affair with editor  &UR; William Shawn &LR; . The Malcolm parody has been
posted on an employee bulletin board at the magazine. The opening
passage, as quoted in the New York Observer:
</P>
<P>
   ``The second time I slept with Mr. Shawn, he asked me to call
him Bill. ... I want the world to know that it was  &LR; me &LR;  Mr. Shawn
loved, and not Miss Ross.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Getting and Having
</P>
<P>
   _ The 100 presenters and participants in Academy Awards
ceremonies, targeted by an array of purveyors wanting to call their
attention to their products, each received a gift basket weighing
57 pounds, says Luxe magazine.
</P>
<P>
   ``The talent work for us gratis,'' said Oscar associate producer
 &UR; Michael Seligman &LR; , ``and we wanted to say thank you with something
more than a sweatshirt and a hat.'' For every 30 products in the
basket, he said, 30 more _ from companies desperate to have their
goods worn by the stars _ were rejected. A partial list of
contents:
</P>
<P>
   Absolut vodka, Bulgari's fragrance, a Christofle silver letter
tray,  &UR; Frederic Fekkai &LR;  day of beauty,  &UR; Harry Winston &LR;  sterling
compass, a JBL stereo CD system, a Montblanc fountain pen,
Ferragamo silk scarf and Tag Heuer chronograph watch.
</P>
<P>
   _ A photo of San Francisco Mayor  &UR; Willie Brown &LR;  talking on the
telephone goes on display Friday at ``Work, Life, Tools,'' an
exhibition of tools that successful people deem essential. The
show, which is at the Embarcadero Skydeck until July 2, is
sponsored by Steelcase Design, which makes office furniture. Among
the other local stars featured are  &UR; Francis Ford Coppola &LR; , who
likes his portable computer, and restaurateur  &UR; Drew &LR; 
 &UR; Nieporent &LR; , who likes Teflon cooking utensils. A portion of the
proceeds goes to LEAP, which helps business and arts programs in
San Francisco public schools.
</P>
<P>
   _ If Erick hasn't already heard it, Good Samaritan  &UR; Mark &LR; 
 &UR; Barbeau &LR;  has enlisted Personals to help spread the word: A
handwritten sign taped to a pole across the street from the jewelry
mart at Eighth and Brannan reads, ``Erick, return the ring! She's
having doubts.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; _  &UR; Bob Riordan &LR; , a man who knows how to put two and two
together, wonders whether it's more than a coincidence that the
Southern Baptists declared that women should be submissive
``immediately after the Viagra explosion.'' &UR; Jerry Matters &LR; , another
guy keeping his eye on the headlines, &UR;  &LR; is imagining `` &UR; Alice
Waters &LR;  offering  &UR; Willie &LR;   &UR; Brown &LR; 's bottled water at her restaurant
in the Louvre as  &UR; Jerry Brown &LR;  walks on water just for the
halibut.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Monica Lewinsky &LR; 's handlers told U.S. News &AMP; World Report
that she has taken up knitting.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Sara Hamlen &LR;  reports that the 18-year-old triplets working
together for the summer at Grace Baking on Solano Avenue in Oakland
are named  &UR; Veni &LR; ,  &UR; Vidi &LR;  and  &UR; Vici Jumana &LR; . They start City College
in San Francisco this fall.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Paul McCartney &LR; ,  &UR; Ringo Starr &LR;  and  &UR; George Harrison &LR; , having
lifted their voices together at Linda McCartney's funeral service,
are talking about putting out an album _ perhaps with
 &UR; Elton John &LR;  and  &UR; Sting &LR;  _ to benefit animal rights, reports the New
York Post.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; ``Q: You've acted in films opposite (Jim) Carrey, Anthony
Hopkins, Brad Pitt and Harrison Ford and Robert De Niro. That must
be quite intimidating. A: When you're sitting opposite someone of
that caliber, you relax. Because their face is so familiar, it
feels like you're sitting with a relative. Then you realize that
they're recognizable because you've seen them in the movies all the
time.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Natascha McElhone in Details magazine.
</P>
