are talking about putting out an album _ perhaps with
 &UR; Elton John &LR;  and  &UR; Sting &LR;  _ to benefit animal rights, reports the New
York Post.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; ``Q: You've acted in films opposite (Jim) Carrey, Anthony
Hopkins, Brad Pitt and Harrison Ford and Robert De Niro. That must
be quite intimidating. A: When you're sitting opposite someone of
that caliber, you relax. Because their face is so familiar, it
feels like you're sitting with a relative. Then you realize that
they're recognizable because you've seen them in the movies all the
time.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Natascha McElhone in Details magazine.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
