<P>
   RAMSEY-COLUMN-HONGKONG (Seattle) _ A year ago, as Britain handed
over Hong Kong to China, the conventional wisdom was that the
territory's civic freedom would be in trouble but its economy
unaffected. That was exactly backward. Today the scorecard on Hong
Kong reads: civic freedom, unaffected; economy, in trouble.
</P>
<P>
   By Bruce Ramsey. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
