happened? History answers the first. Historical simulations, like
the computer game Gettysburg, answer the second. By J.C. Herz.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-PERSONAL-POLLS (Undated) _ Cynthia Lewis, it is fair to say,
is an extremely curious person. In the past five months, she has
conducted 44 opinion polls on questions ranging from the political
(``Should President Clinton be impeached?'') to the personal
(``Which smell do you prefer in a lover?'') to the philosophical
(``How often do you behave according to your ideals?''). So far her
polls have prompted more than 2,000 responses. Ms. Lewis, a senior
at Hood College in Maryland, is a regular participant on a Web site
called Survey Central, which lets her create online polls on any
subject she desires. By Pamela Li Calzi O'Connell. Photo.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-POETRY (Undated) _ A computer program that let's you compose
poetry with language fragments on your screen that look like
refrigerator magnets. By Lisa Napoli. Photo.
</P>
<P>
