<HEADLINE>
FATHER'S DAY GIFT GUIDE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BARBARA DE WITT 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ &UR;  &LR; Sometimes ``Thanks'' just isn't enough. To
celebrate Father's Day, give Dad the day off, and maybe a little
token of your appreciation.
</P>
<P>
   Since time is running out _ Father's Day is Sunday _ we shopped
for you. Here's our list of fun and frivolous gifts, starting with
the smallest of budgets.
</P>
<P>
   79 cents _ Quart of Mobil oil to keep his car engine running
smoothly, at Kmart.
</P>
<P>
   $5 _ Red Schick Protector razor, at Wal-Mart and Kmart stores.
</P>
<P>
   $5 _ Spin Science, a psychedelic time-warp toy to remind him of
``Grateful Dead'' days, at Store of Knowledge, Brookstone and
Natural Wonders.
</P>
<P>
   $6 _ Docker socks to replace those heel-less pairs, at Sears.
</P>
<P>
   $9.99 _ A voice-memo key chain recorder to help him find the car
at Dodger Stadium, at RadioShack.
</P>
<P>
   $10 _ Red Dolphin gas can for his car (just in case he runs out
of gas), at Restoration Hardware stores.
</P>
<P>
   $10 _ A pair of matinee tickets for the two of you to laugh
through ``Godzilla.''
</P>
<P>
   $15 _ Box of cigars that won't damage his lungs, at See's
Candies stores.
</P>
<P>
   $18 _ Fossil's really small leather cash clip, at Robinsons-May.
</P>
<P>
   $19.99 _ Looney Tunes golf set (towel, balls and tees), at
Mervyn's.
</P>
<P>
   $19.99 _ Ralph Lauren bath sheets featuring golfers or bikers,
at Macy's.
</P>
<P>
   $19.99 _ Lionel Collectible train watch with lifelike train
