   CLINTON-DAVIS (Washington) _ California Lt. Gov. Gray Davis, who
clinched the Democratic nomination for governor June 2, meets with
President Clinton at the White House. Davis says that despite
controversies surrounding the White House, he believes the
president will be ``an asset'' to his campaign against Republican
Dan Lungren. By DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   TEXANS-MONEY (Washington) _ Seeking to shore up support for the
fall elections, Texas' gubernatorial candidates are cuddling up to
special interests at fund-raisers in the nation's capital. Gov.
George W. Bush, a Republican, is expected to raise $750,000 and
Texas Land Commissioner Garry Mauro, a Democrat, will cash in on
his 25-year friendship with President Clinton at a reception that
is expected to raise $350,000. By GARY MARTIN.
</P>
<P>
   ONASSIS-AWARDS (Washington) _ Hospice care crusader Rose Crumb
of Port Angeles, Wash., receives the Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis
Award for public service as the founder of the volunteer Hospice of
Clallam County. By MARK HELM.
</P>
