   INTERNATIONAL NEWS (``i'' category)
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-LEADERLESS (Paris) _ already filed _ Western governments
have demanded that Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto
initiate sweeping reforms designed to rescue his country's sagging
economy before it drags down the rest of the world. But the problem
is that Hashimoto, like most of his predecessors, lacks the
authority and prestige even to contemplate such a task. By BERNARD
D. KAPLAN.
