<P>
   She asks the doctors the important questions. She makes most of
the over-the-counter pharmaceutical purchases. She monitors the
health and well-being of the entire family. In most households, the
woman is the healthcare gatekeeper.
</P>
<P>
   Recognizing this, The New York Times is publishing a special
stand-alone news section on June 21 titled ``WOMEN'S HEALTH,''
which covers a range of health issues and addresses every stage of
a woman's life.
</P>
<P>
   Starting THURSDAY, JUNE 18, THE NEW YORK TIMES SYNDICATE will be
offering for one-shot purchase a selection of features _ plus art _
from this section that will help your readers understand the
medical innovations and trends that affect women's lives _ and the
lives of those around them.
</P>
<P>
   PLEASE NOTE: The stories, which will appear in The Times on June
21, can be purchased starting June 18 and can be published June 21
or anytime thereafter.
</P>
