<P>
   DOLLAR-YEN (Washington) - President Clinton ordered the United
States to quickly begin buying yen to stop the precipitous fall of
the Japanese currency, after his top economic advisers warned that
Japan's mounting economic problems _ and its slow response _ were
threatening China and other nations. By David E. Sanger
</P>
<P>
   OIL-SMUGGLE (Washington) Large volumes of oil are being smuggled
in violation of the sanctions and the Clinton administration is
ignoring it. By James Risen BLAIR-ACCENT (London) _ Tony Blair is a
prime minister who prides himself on his common touch, so there was
nothing particularly surprising about what he said recently on a
British talk show. What was surprising were the Prime Minister's
missing T's? And what happened to his H's? Why, when he tried to
say, ``they put on a little show for us with the mayor of the
little village,'' did it come out as, ``they pu' on a li'l show for
us with they mayor of the li'l village?'' By Sarah Lyall
</P>
