</P>
<P>
   CONGRESS-TOBACCO _ The Senate will probably take a conclusive
vote on the tobacco bill today or tonight, but what and when are
not clear. All sorts of huddles going on as noses are being
counted. By David E. Rosenbaum.
</P>
<P>
   CONGRESS-TAXES (Washington) _ After years of rhetoric about the
complexities and inequities in the tax code, the House today took a
dramatic if almost wholly symbolic step towards doing something
about it. It voted to require that Congress come up with a new tax
system within four years and scrap the current code by the end of
2002. By Richard W. Stevenson.
