<HEADLINE>
BETTER TO LIGHT ONE CANDLE 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ It's true that everything looks better by
candlelight. Besides, it beats eating in the dark. But there are
hazards: in cooperation with the Consumer Product Safety
Commission, Conros Corp. of Toronto has recalled 30,000 fuel
canisters for its Summer Lights outdoor bamboo torches. The plastic
canisters can cause the bamboo poles to ignite.
</P>
<P>
   If you bought a canister in April and May of this year, and it
says ``Summer Lights Torch ... Refillable Fuel Canister,'' call
Conros at (800) 988-3956 for a refund or a replacement.
</P>
<P>
   There is a new, safer tiki light: a 67-inch-tall stainless steel
model with a fiberglass wick that comes with a refillable canister.
It sells for $70 from the Williams Sonoma catalog, (800) 541-2233.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
