<HEADER>
A4048 &Cx1f; tth-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI &LR;      06-17 0213
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Thursday, June 18, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Tina May at (206) 448-8355.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SONICS (Seattle) Hiring of Paul Westphal as head Sonics
coach is announced Wednesday at news confernce. Westphal and Sonic
President Wally Walker comment for the first time.
</P>
<P>
   By Ronald Tillery. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   with: BKN-SONICS-WEST (Undated) A profile of Westphal through
the eyes of those who played for him in his last head-coaching job,
at Phoenix, and maybe from his buddy Rush Limbaugh.
</P>
<P>
   By Jim Moore. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-COLUMN-THIEL (Seattle) On the Sonics hiring Paul Westphal.
</P>
<P>
   By Art Thiel. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GLF-USOPEN (San Francisco) U.S. Open starts Thursday at Olympic
Golf Course, San Francisco, probably involving defending champ
Ernie Els and Seattle's Fred Couples, this season's leading money
winner.
</P>
<P>
   By Angelo Bruscas. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Anaheim) Mariners at Anaheim.
</P>
<P>
   By Jim Street. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
