<HEADLINE>
COMPANY NEWS 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Merchants Mutual Insurance Co., Buffalo, N.Y., held preliminary
discussions about acquiring the shares of Merchants Group Inc.,
Buffalo, that it does not already own. Merchants Group is the
parent of a property casualty insurer called Merchants Insurance
Co. of New Hampshire Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Levitz Furniture Corp., Boca Raton, Fla., a home-furniture
retailer, said it would close 13 stores in St. Louis, San Diego,
Denver and Orlando and Tampa, Fla., and open new stores in the New
York, Los Angeles, Seattle and Philadelphia areas.
</P>
<P>
   Royal Ahold NV, the Netherlands' biggest retailer, extended its
$2.7 billion takeover bid for Giant Food Inc., by a month after
securing only about 55 percent of outstanding shares before the
original Wednesday deadline. The $43.50-a-share offer will run
until July 15. &QL;
</P>
