<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On Deck: Florida Marlins
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 1:10 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Turner Field.
</P>
<P>
   TV/radio: Fox Sports South, 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: LHP Tom Glavine (9-2, 2.68; 5-6,
3.56 lifetime vs. Marlins) vs. RHP Ryan Dempster (0-2, 10.20; first
appearance vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Glavine is collecting some payback from 1997, when he had
12 non-decisions. Not only does he have just two NDs during his
first 14 starts, but the team has responded on the few nights when
he has been vulnerable. In the three games Glavine has given up
four runs or more, he is 1-1; other Braves starters are 3-10 when
yielding four or more. Although he is unbeaten in his last seven
starts, he is coming off a 9-7 victory over Montreal, when he
allowed a season-high 11 hits. Glavine has worked into the seventh
inning in 10 games, in part because of some excellent run support
(6.1 runs per game). Dempster, making his fourth major-league
start, is coming off an excellent showing against New York last
Friday, when he limited the Mets to one earned run in seven
innings. A Canadian from Gibsons, British Columbia, Dempster
originally was property of the Texas Rangers, who picked him in the
third round of the 1995 draft. Texas traded him to the Marlins a
year later as part of the John Burkett deal. Just 10-9 last season
while pitching at Class A Brevard County, Dempster has been hurt in
the majors by left-handers, who are hitting .444 against him with
11 walks and four homers in just 27 at-bats.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
