From 1952 to 1966, Ozzie and Harriet were America's ideal fantasy
couple in the 1950s. ``That family loomed so large in America's
psyche,'' says Jones. ``What made this documentary unusual is that
the family, which lived so much of their their lives on television,
chose to work through some very private feelings in the same
forum.'' (Steve Goldstein/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT9) UNDATED -- June 17, 1998 -- HOME-IMPROVEMENT, 6-17 -- A
file is a relatively simple tool, a piece of hardened steel with
teeth cut across the surface, using it should be fairly
straightforward and easy.(Edward R. Lipinski/New York Times Photo)
*LITE
</P>
