<HEADLINE>
CARDINALS SIGN SEVENTH-ROUND PICK 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, ARIZ. - The Cardinals continue to sign their rookies at a
franchise-record pace.
</P>
<P>
   They came to terms with another draft pick on Wednesday when
Colorado wide receiver  &UR; Phil Savoy, one of four seventh-round
selections, reached agreement on a two-year deal.
</P>
<P>
   Seven of their 10 draft picks have signed, all but first-round
choice  &UR; Andre Wadsworth, Florida State defensive end;
second-rounder
 &UR; Corey Chavous, Vanderbilt defensive back; and seventh-rounder  &UR; Pat
 &UR; Tillman, the Arizona State linebacker who is being converted to
safety.
</P>
<P>
   Terms of Savoy's deal were not disclosed, but sources close to
the negotiations said he received a package worth about $380,000.
The Cardinals earlier offered Savoy a signing bonus of $24,000,
with annual salaries of $158,000 and $198,000.
</P>
<P>
   Savoy said he would have reached agreement much sooner had his
agent,  &UR; Michael George, not suffered a heart attack shortly after
last April's draft.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm pretty pleased,'' said Savoy, the only wide receiver the
team drafted. ``If I just keep working hard, push myself and stay
focused, I think I've got a chance to make this team.''
</P>
<P>
   The Cardinals also signed veteran free-agent cornerback  &UR; Dexter
 &UR; Seigler, who played for Amsterdam of the NFL Europe League this
spring. He spent parts of the previous three seasons with the
Seattle Seahawks. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Comfort zone &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Kevin Drake's career as a wide receiver almost ended after two
games last season.
</P>
<P>
   He had just dropped four passes for Alabama-Birmingham against
the University of Memphis and wondered if he should return to
quarterback.
</P>
<P>
   A year later, he's trying to win a receiving job in the NFL.
</P>
<P>
   ``After the Memphis game, the coach called me to the front of
the bus and said, `Are you sure we made the right move? It's not
too late to move you back,' '' Drake said.
</P>
<P>
   His season changed when he had seven catches for 144 yards the
third game of the season at Arizona.
</P>
<P>
   ``That was a breakthrough game,'' he said. ``Before that, it was
looking like a bad move.''
</P>
<P>
   He finished with 38 catches for 823 yards (21.7 average) and
seven touchdowns and was chosen second-team All-Conference USA.
</P>
<P>
   The Cardinals signed Drake, 6 foot 3, 187 pounds, as an
undrafted free agent, and he's competing for the fifth receiver
spot.
</P>
<P>
   ``I never thought I'd be here,'' he said of Cardinals rookie
camp. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Cap and gown
</P>
<P>
   Rookie  &UR; Zack Walz left rookie camp last week to attend
graduation ceremonies at Dartmouth.
</P>
<P>
   He already was exhausted from a six-hour plane fight. Then, it
started raining during the commencement exercises, and Dartmouth
officials refused to move graduation inside.
</P>
<P>
   ``They don't cancel it unless there is lightning,'' said Walz, a
sixth-round pick who graduated from the Ivy League school with a
degree in government. ``So, we sat out there for four hours in the
rain. I was on the verge of catching pneumonia.''
</P>
<P>
   The bad weather delayed Walz's flight back to the Valley from
Boston. He didn't arrive until 3 a.m. Monday, a few hours before he
had to report to the Cardinals' Tempe training facility for a
meeting. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Short shots
</P>
<P>
   How did rookie quarterback  &UR; Cory Sauter of Minnesota spend his
honeymoon last month? He and his wife,  &UR; Amy, visited the national
parks, including the Grand Canyon, on his trip from Minneapolis to
the Valley.
</P>
<P>
   Offensive tackle  &UR; Anthony Clement, one of two second-round
picks, signed a three-year deal worth $1.94 million, including a
$710,000 signing bonus.
</P>
<P>
   Tight end  &UR; Terry Hardy, a fifth-round pick from Southern
Mississippi, signed a one-year deal worth $195,000. He received a
$35,000 signing bonus. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
